main event: A witness observed an oblong, star-like object that was greenish-blue and giving off color in Twig, Minnesota on March 20, 1966.
interesting points: The object moved up and down and in a slight circle.
The object was observed for 21 minutes.
The witness used binoculars to observe the object.
The object was seen at an elevation of 7 degrees above the horizon.
The weather conditions were clear with unlimited visibility.
result: The object was concluded to be the star Arcturus.
sighted object: an oblong, star-like object that was greenish-blue and giving off color
photographs: No photographs were included in the report.
